does god hear the cries of your heart do not be anxious about anything but in everything by prayer and petition with thanksgiving present your request to god and the peace of god which transends all understanding will guard your hearts and your minds in christ jesus philippians good morning and have a blessed day yes abselutely in the same way the spirit also comes to help us weak as we are for we do not know how we ought to pray the spirit himself pleads with god for us in groans that words cannot express and god who sees into our hearts knows what the thought of the spirit is because the spirit pleads with god on behalf of his people and in accordance with his will we know that in all things god works for good with those who love him those whom he has called according to his purpose Epistle to the Philippians Christian eschatology Comparing and contrasting Judaism and Christianity Amidah Sola fide Holy Spirit Book of Mormon Eastern Orthodox Church Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Roman Catholic Church Historical roots of Catholic Eucharistic theology Mary, the mother of Jesus Justification (theology) God the Father Prayer Ten Commandments John Howard Yoder Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints Book of Isaiah Jewish services John the Baptist Salvation God Merit Eucharist Community of Christ Church of Christ, Scientist Binitarianism Intercession of saints Five points of Calvinism God and gender Religious Society of Friends Tridentine Mass Angel Godhead (Mormonism) Opus Dei Charles Grandison Finney Trinity Blessed Virgin Mary Mass (liturgy) Psychopannychism Priesthood (Mormonism) Rule of St Benedict Idolatry in Christianity Perseverance of the saints First Book of Nephi Good Friday Prayer Virgin Mary in Islam Sin Christian views of Jesus Soul Holy water Repentance Thanksgiving Didache Mortification of the flesh Teresa of Avila Original sin John Wycliffe Philipp Melanchthon Rastafari movement Origen God Save the Queen Godspell Criticisms of Charisma